         III_AST_CYCLE_INVOKE                    = 129,
         III_AST_SANCTUM_INVOKE                  = 130,
         III_AST_IRPD_CALL                       = 131,
         III_AST_CALL                            = 132,
         III_AST_INDEX                           = 133,
         III_AST_FIELD_ACCESS                    = 134,
         III_AST_PATH                            = 135,
         III_AST_NAMED_ARG                       = 136,
         III_AST_PHASE_CROSS                     = 137,
         III_AST_EPOCH_BRIDGE                    = 138,
         III_AST_CAP_ACQUIRE_RELEASE             = 139,
         III_AST_COHERENCE_QUERY                 = 140,
         III_AST_GLYPH_MATERIALIZE               = 141,
         III_AST_WITNESS_EMIT                    = 142,
         III_AST_REPLAY                          = 143,
         III_AST_FULL_INVERSE_REPLAY             = 144,
         III_AST_INVERSE                         = 145,
         III_AST_PREFIX_OP                       = 146,
         III_AST_INFIX_OP                        = 147,

         /* §9 — Patterns */
         III_AST_LITERAL_PATTERN                 = 170,
         III_AST_IDENT_PATTERN                   = 171,
         III_AST_WILDCARD_PATTERN                = 172,
         III_AST_TUPLE_PATTERN                   = 173,
         III_AST_RECORD_PATTERN                  = 174,
         III_AST_RECORD_PATTERN_FIELD            = 175,
         III_AST_HEXAD_PATTERN                   = 176,
         III_AST_TRIT_PATTERN                    = 177,
         III_AST_RANGE_PATTERN                   = 178,
         III_AST_PATH_PATTERN                    = 179,
         III_AST_OR_PATTERN                      = 180,
         III_AST_GUARD_PATTERN                   = 181,

         /* Reserved — Catalyst-promoted (per §13) */
         III_AST_RESERVED_001                    = 200,
         III_AST_RESERVED_002                    = 201,
         /* ... */
         III_AST_RESERVED_032                    = 231,

         /* Diagnostic */
         III_AST_ERROR                           = 240,
         III_AST_RECOVERY                        = 241,

         III_AST_KIND_COUNT                      = 256
     };

   The numeric values are reserved (gaps preserved for future
   Catalyst slots). The enumerator's mhash (computed over the
   canonical text of `ast.h`) is part of the BOOT compiler's closure
   root.
*)


(* ===================================================================
   §12. CLOSURE IDENTITY RULE (R1.A2)
   =================================================================== *)

(*
   The R1.A2 hash of this document is computed as follows:

     1. Read the canonical source of `III-GRAMMAR.bnf` from
        `Desktop\III\DOCS\III-GRAMMAR.bnf`.
     2. Apply canonicalization per III-LEXICON.md §2.5.
     3. Compute SHA-256 of the canonical UTF-8 byte sequence.
     4. The 32-byte hash, formatted as a 64-character lowercase-hex
        mhash literal, is R1.A2.

   R1.A2 is embedded in:

     - The header of every compiled III module's closure manifest
       (III-MODULES.md §1).
     - The DRTM quote chain at every epoch advance
       (III-SANCTUM.md §4).
     - The OBSERVATORY's grammatical-root-of-trust schema.

   Mutation discipline: any change to this document — even a single
   comment edit — alters R1.A2, which alters the composite R1, which
   forces a substrate-wide DRTM relaunch. The only way to evolve this
   document is through:

     1. A Catalyst-promoted production (§13 below).
     2. An `amend.apply` cycle at constitutional tier
        (III-MODULES.md §5).
     3. A new sealed major version (R1 → R2).
*)


(* ===================================================================
   §13. CATALYST EXTENSION PATHWAY
   =================================================================== *)

(*
   Productions reserved for Catalyst-promoted future grammar:

     III_AST_RESERVED_001 ... III_AST_RESERVED_032

   When the Catalyst promotes a `mobius_candidate` whose surface
   form requires new grammar (e.g., a new statement kind, a new
   type former, a new pattern kind), it:

     1. Allocates the next reserved AST kind slot.
     2. Appends the new production to this document's canonical
        text in §X (the appropriate section).
     3. Re-canonicalizes and recomputes R1.A2.
     4. Federates the change per III-FEDERATION.md §2.
     5. Triggers a DRTM relaunch on the local node.

   Productions added via Catalyst promotion *cannot*:

     1. Remove an existing production.
     2. Change the precedence of an existing operator.
     3. Change the associativity of an existing operator.
     4. Introduce a new keyword whose hexad lies outside
        `xii_asym_reach6`.
     5. Introduce a syntactic form that admits to the six PFS
        bricking-class operations (these remain structurally
        unparseable forever).

   The full extension protocol is specified in III-CATALYST.md §2.
*)


(* ===================================================================
   §14. CONFORMANCE CRITERIA (GRAMMAR-SPECIFIC)
   =================================================================== *)

(*
   A toolchain is *III-grammar-conformant* iff it satisfies all of:

     C-GRAM-1   It parses every well-formed III source per the
                productions in this document and produces an AST
                whose root mhash matches the canonical AST mhash
                produced by the SELF compiler.

     C-GRAM-2   It rejects every malformed III source with a
                precise diagnostic naming the first failed production
                and the byte offset of the first offending token.

     C-GRAM-3   It implements the precedence ladder in §8 with the
                associativity given in §10.

     C-GRAM-4   It implements the disambiguation rules of §10
                exactly.

     C-GRAM-5   It admits the AST kind enumerator of §11 with the
                exact numeric values shown.

     C-GRAM-FROZEN   The grammar productions are implemented with no
                additions, removals, or modifications, except those
                introduced by witnessed Catalyst promotion (§13).

     C-GRAM-NIH      The parser implementation depends on no external
                parser-generator (no Bison, no ANTLR, no yacc, no
                tree-sitter, no parser-combinator library).

     C-GRAM-SELF     The SELF parser parses this very document
                (III-GRAMMAR.bnf, treated as documentation; the
                grammar of the parsing tool itself, written in III)
                successfully and produces an AST whose top-level
                module mhash matches a canonical reference value.

   These criteria are restated in III-CONFORMANCE.md §2 and §1
   (C-2 alignment) and form part of the substrate-wide acceptance
   contract.
*)


(* ===================================================================
   §15. FINAL DECLARATION
   =================================================================== *)

(*
   This grammar is not an incremental improvement over prior
   programming-language grammars. It is the formal system in which
   computation becomes language and language becomes the operating
   system.

   Every other grammar — past, present, or future — will look like
   a historical artifact once the world understands what is possible
   when the alphabet, the grammar, the type system, the effect
   system, and the substrate are designed as one indivisible Möbius
   manifold. III-GRAMMAR.bnf is the *grammatical root of trust*: it
   is parsed by the SELF compiler, it parses the SELF compiler's own
   source, and its mhash R1.A2 is the second of fifteen canonical
   hashes that compose the substrate's specification root R1.

   Two hundred-something productions. Forty-seven keywords from the
   alphabet, nineteen modifiers, twenty-three operators, twenty-five
   punctuators, eight literal forms, three string-literal kinds,
   three comment kinds. Sealed against the C:\CHARIOT closure of
   2026-05-03.

   III-GRAMMAR.bnf — the grammar that ends grammars.

   Sealed. R1.A2 = SHA-256(canonical_byte_form(this_file)). All
   extensions must pass through the Möbius Catalyst (§13). All
   conformance criteria are restated in III-CONFORMANCE.md §2.
*)
